#Criteria Query

CriteriaBuilder cb = entityManager.getCriteriaBuilder();
CriteriaQuery<User> cq = cb.createQuery(User.class);

Root<User> root = cq.from(User.class);
cq.select(root).where(cb.gt(root.get("age"), 25));

List<User> users = entityManager.createQuery(cq).getResultList();

=> CascadeType.ALL propagates parent entity operations like persist, merge, and delete to child entities. orphanRemoval=true is different because it automatically deletes child entities when they are 
removed from the parent collection. It is mainly used to prevent orphan records in one-to-many relationships where child entities should not exist independently.

=> “Thread starvation occurs when some threads never get execution opportunities because other threads continuously occupy resources, often due to unfair scheduling or blocked thread pools. Thread 
congestion occurs when too many threads compete for limited system resources like CPU or locks, causing excessive context switching and performance degradation. Starvation affects fairness, 
while congestion affects overall throughput and latency.”

